  id: "WI-102",
  description: "Proposal 025.1 Phase 7 — mapping ... -> rule X rule-inline. Per-symbol anthill→Z3 translation; the small-scale workaround for cases where the user knows precisely which rule should be inlined as a Z3 (define-fun ...). Holds the line until a separate simp-set proposal lands. Deliverables: grammar extension to mapping_entry to accept 'name -> rule X' syntax (one-line addition; covered in Phase 2 grammar work, finalised here); emit walks the rule body, translates to Z3 (define-fun ...), prepends to SMT-LIB preamble; recursion through referenced rules. Test: a custom euclidean_dist rule mapped into a proof, discharged unsat. Risks: translation gaps when a rule body uses an operation with no Z3 equivalent (mitigation: surface a clear error pointing at the offending sub-term). See §Implementation plan Phase 7 and §Anthill-rule-aware simplification (deferred).",
